{
  "texts": [
    "Specifically, they propose to use three GCNs to create context-aware feature vectors for each of the object, attribute, and relationship nodes.",
    "The resulting context-aware nodes undergo fusion with the self-attention maps, enabling the model to control the granularity of captions.",
    "Finally, the authors test two methods of training an LSTM-based language generator: the first being a traditional supervised approach with cross-entropy loss and the second being a reinforcement learning-based approach that uses CIDEr [113] as the reward function.",
    "By utilising context dependent GCNs in their architecture, to specifically account for the object, attribute, and relationship nodes, SASG is able to achieve competitive results when compared with similar models, as shown in Table 3.",
    "SGAE (scene graph autoencoder) is another paper to make use of a multi-partite semantic graph."
  ]
}